<p><strong>Till My Last Breath by Durjoy Datta: A Riveting Tale of Love and Resilience</strong></p>
<p><strong>Q: What is the central theme of "Till My Last Breath" by Durjoy Datta?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> The novel explores the themes of love, loss, resilience, and the indomitable spirit of a woman facing adversity. It depicts the protagonist's unwavering determination to find happiness and fulfillment despite the challenges life throws her way.</p>
<p><strong>Q: Who are the main characters in the book?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> The story revolves around Aditi Roy, a young woman from New Delhi who battles cancer. She finds support and love from her fiancé, Abir, and a diverse group of friends and family. The novel also introduces several other characters who play significant roles in Aditi's journey.</p>
<p><strong>Q: What are some of the challenges faced by Aditi in the novel?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Aditi's primary challenge is her battle with cancer, which tests her physical and emotional limits. Throughout the novel, she also grapples with societal stigma, financial difficulties, and the disapproval of her fiancé's family.</p>
<p><strong>Q: How does Aditi overcome these challenges?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Aditi's unwavering optimism, determination, and the support of her loved ones serve as her weapons against adversity. She undergoes treatment, confronts societal prejudices, and learns to navigate the complexities of life with courage and grace.</p>
<p><strong>Q: What is the significance of the title, "Till My Last Breath"?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> The title symbolizes Aditi's indomitable spirit and her refusal to let cancer define her. It encapsulates her belief that she will fight for her happiness and life with every ounce of strength she possesses, regardless of the outcome.</p>